4 FOR
HOUSE BILL NO. 3727 By: Shaw
5
6
7
8 PROPOSED POLICY COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
9 An Act relating to lobbying regulation; prohibiting
former members of Legislature from registering as
10 lobbyists for certain period; providing exemption for
former members of Legislature registered as lobbyists
11 before certain date; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Rule 5.30, Appendix I of Title 74,
17 unless there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as
18 follows:
19 Beginning on November 1, 2026, no former member of the Oklahoma
20 House of Representatives or the Oklahoma State Senate may work or
21 register as a lobbyist until four (4) years after their last term
22 has expired. This act shall not apply to former members of the
23 Legislature who have become registered lobbyists prior to November
24 1, 2026.
Req. No. 16303 Page 1

1 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
